  <title class="- topic/title ">Creating a Campaign: Overview</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Creating a campaign typically involves
	 several steps. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
    <context id="context_FB9947CB6EAA47E98F926EFC580F532D" class="- topic/section task/context ">
      <p class="- topic/p ">
        <ol id="ol_0D80D517AB6C4A0D8D2AEC8962A8D590" class="- topic/ol ">
          <li id="li_C0FA8B30BF1B45C59CB34768AD93EB75" class="- topic/li "> Name
			 the campaign, set start and end dates, set a priority, and configure the
			 targeting rules governing who sees this campaigns content. 
			 <p class="- topic/p ">With the exception of the campaign, all
				settings have appropriate defaults that simplify this step. 
			 </p></li>
          <li id="li_F48F2279296A41FBA8FF2A7F4B9EE45B" class="- topic/li ">
			 Select the locations where the campaign's content appears. 
			 <p class="- topic/p ">Locations are the mboxes on your site. 
			 </p></li>
          <li id="li_979488A4FAF3486EBA83F9659F97B212" class="- topic/li ">
			 Create experiences and assign offers to your locations for each experience. 
			 <p class="- topic/p ">You can also assign targeting rules to
				different experiences. 
			 </p></li>
          <li id="li_929D23784B604489832F58A80BF11476" class="- topic/li ">
			 Select your success metrics, which measure the effectiveness of your campaign. 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_E5E48960FBE24D44833A2A9546BB731E" class="- topic/li "> Apply
			 any segment filters to your campaign. 
			 <p class="- topic/p ">Segments filters allow you to analyze campaign
				effectiveness for different types of visitors. 
			 </p></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To create a
			 campaign</b>
      </p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_5EB2E5CC3E7B4A669F570EBA9996DB33" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
      <step id="step_9A2B98CA83524F3087D7BF3C2F64FA03" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To create a campaign, click 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Campaigns</uicontrol>
			 &gt; 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Create</uicontrol>,
			 then select the type of campaign you want to create. . 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_1B7273F35741491A8BDF690E43140014" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Configure the campaign as explained
			 in 
			 <xref href="c_Changing_Campaign_Settings.xml#concept_D70808CDA2524DCA857004DAED110F27" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref "><?xm-replace_text Changing Campaign Settings?></xref></cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
